<FlowDocument PagePadding="5,0,5,0" AllowDrop="True" NumberSubstitution.CultureSource="User" xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"><Paragraph><Run FontFamily="Verdana" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="13.3333333333333" xml:space="preserve">External Text in </Run><Run FontFamily="Verdana" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="13.3333333333333" xml:lang="en-ca">Watermark</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="13.3333333333333">If you simply use watermark text box below, you get same texts to all the images within the project. This feature is designed to allow the images within same project could have different watermark texts.</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="13.3333333333333" xml:space="preserve">This is done via an external controlling file. </Run></Paragraph><List MarkerStyle="Disc"><ListItem><Paragraph><Run FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="13.3333333333333">The controlling file should have same name of image file, for example, if the image file is named something.jpg then the controlling file must be something.txt. Each individual image file can have its own controlling file.</Run></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="13.3333333333333">Each controlling file is allowed to have any number of controlling tag - one tag one line.</Run></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="13.3333333333333" xml:space="preserve">The tag line begins with "{{" following by a tag name, closed by "}}", after the tag name you can have any texts without line break. For example: </Run><Run FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="13.3333333333333"><Run.TextDecorations><TextDecoration Location="Underline" /></Run.TextDecorations>{{TagName1}} This is a piece of text</Run><Run FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="13.3333333333333">.</Run></Paragraph></ListItem></List><Paragraph><Run FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="13.3333333333333">If you want to insert external text into your watermark, focus on text box below, move cursor to desire position and click "Insert External Text" button. It will give you an empty tag "{{}}". from there you are free to enter any tag defined in external controlling file described above.</Run></Paragraph></FlowDocument>